caption: How they have a 4.0 I have no idea. We are here now  Friday at 1:50. They have no food! They have 21 trays a couple of different chicken and beef! The rest is veggies, potatos, rice, they have a egg roll all cabbage the spring roll stuffed with the same cabbage. The taste of the food is okay. Not bad not great. It is a $5.00 buffet or 10 for two and it cost 18.50 to get out of here!! Go to CHOW TYME NOT THE GREATEST EITHER BUT 100 TIMES BETTER THAN THIS.
This was a good place to grab some food. The selection is small based off of some other locations. However what they lacked in options they did make up in flavor.

The worse General Tso chicken. I have ever had. Tasted burnt and very little flavor have been visiting husband in hosp for almost 3 weeks  and was a little tired of their food but thus was worse than hospital food. Sorry I wasted my money 11.00 went in the trash

Went by to pick up dinner to go. Buffet is going downhill. Nothing, no veggies, onions, etc. In fried rice. Very few cashews in cashew chicken. Used to have several beef or pork mixed dishes. Now only one and it is sad. Egg rolls are tough and not crispy. Just really disappointed.
Want fried shrimp back.

MY RECOMMENDATION... DONT WASTE YOUR TIME OR TASTE BUDS!!!  This place is over 19 years old. It looks like the walls , carpet, bathroom have not been cleaned or updated in all those 19 years. I came here about 2 years ago thinking maybe they would have done a little cleaning or updating.... nope. I should have learned my lesson but I decided to give them a second/third chance..... NEEDLESS TO SAY, NO MORE CHANCES HERE. It is just plain GROSS.

After speaking with a manager they charge me for a bowl of soup and the sweet tea. Which is still half the price of a Buffet ! So very disappointed in the service of handling the charge of soup and tea I’m very disappointed in the quality of the food today I don’t mind paying for soup and tea did I did eat and drink but I just feel it was too costly for that little bit of food

I was looking for a good place that was closer then Pace and when a friend said it was good, I was excited to try it but I can't see a situation that I would pick to go there again. Sorry, I know everyone is hurting during covid. First, I guess their printer jammed so despite the fact that I ordered online so we didn't have to wait there during covid they never noticed until I showed up for the order. Then they gave me egg drop soup, which I can't stand, instead of the hot & sour soup I order, money down the drain. I guess the food is edible but I wouldn't say it was good. It wasn't even good enough to keep the left over. My dining partner wasn't a fan either. He ate his food but said "let's not go back" Three strikes and they are out

Shanghai buffet never disappoints. Don't go here if you need 300 different items, this by no means is huge buffet but options available are really good. I choose this place over all others in town because each dish actually taste different then the one next to it. Really good fried rice and lo mein . All of you complaining about going now during covid lol smh WOW who would eat at a buffet during this.  Do yourself a favor order you some for takeout and have your own clean safe buffet at home..

Do not waste your time on this place. I really can't believe they are open. I was very disappointed. I received a bill for thirty dollars for just myself and granddaughter.
